LOGIN FUNCTIONALITY					

Environment: QA/Staging  |  Pre-conditions: User has a registered and verified account.					
					
Test Case ID	Scenario / Description	Test Steps	Expected Result	Type	Priority
TC_LOGIN_001	Verify successful login with valid credentials.	
1. Navigate to Login page.
2. Enter valid Email.
3. Enter valid Password.
4. Click 'Login'	User is successfully authenticated and redirected to the Dashboard/Home page.	Positive	High

TC_LOGIN_002	Verify login fails with an unregistered email address.
1. Enter an email not in the system.
2. Enter any password.
3. Click 'Login'	System displays error message: 'Invalid email or password.' User remains on login page.	Negative	High

TC_LOGIN_003	Verify login fails with a wrong password.	"1. Enter a valid registered email.
2. Enter an incorrect password.
3. Click 'Login'	System displays error message: 'Invalid email or password.' password field is cleared.	Negative	High

TC_LOGIN_004	Verify login validation when fields are left blank.	"1. Leave Email and Password fields empty.
2. Click 'Login'	Inline validation messages appear: 'Email is required' and 'Password is required'.	Negative	Medium

TC_LOGIN_005	Verify account lockout after 5 consecutive failed attempts.	"1. Enter valid email but wrong password 5 times in a row.
2. Click 'Login' on the 5th time."	Account is temporarily locked. Message displays: 'Account locked for 15 minutes due to multiple failed attempts.'	Edge Case	High

TC_LOGIN_006	Verify password field masking (security check).	1. Type characters into the Password input field.	Characters are masked/hidden as dots (●●●●●) or asterisks for privacy.	Positive	Medium
TC_LOGIN_007	Verify login functionality handles SQL Injection attempts safely.	
1. Enter ' OR '1'='1 in the email/password field.
2. Click 'Login'	System rejects the input safely with a standard validation error. No database data is leaked.	Edge Case	High

TC_LOGIN_008	Verify 'Show Password' toggle functionality.	"1. Enter text in the Password field.
2. Click the eye icon/toggle button."	Masked characters become plain text. Clicking again masks them again.	Positive	Low
TC_LOGIN_009	Verify form submission using the 'Enter' keyboard key.	"1. Enter valid Email and Password.

2. Press the 'Enter' key on the keyboard instead of clicking 'Login'."	Form submits successfully and authenticates the user just like clicking the button.	Positive	Medium
TC_LOGIN_010	Verify text inputs trim accidental leading/trailing spaces.	"1. Enter valid email with a space at the end ('user@email.com ').
2. Enter valid password.
3. Click 'Login'	System trims the whitespace automatically and logs the user in successfully.	Edge Case	Medium
